<div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:16px 18px;">
<h3 data-pasted="true"><span style="color: rgb(14, 30, 61);"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;">Handover Deliverables List</span></strong></span></h3>
<p><span style="color: rgb(14, 30, 61);"><strong><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);" data-pasted="true">The following deliverables include information required at Practical Completion, during the Defects Liability Period, and through early operational use, as defined in the Project Information Requirements and Scope.</span></span></strong></span></p>
<p class="p1" data-pasted="true"><span style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136); font-family: &quot;Open sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; display: inline !important;">The Lead Appointed Party, operator, operations team or facility manager</span><span style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);"> should provide the Appointing Party with the following, as a minimum:</span></p>
<ul class="froala-checkbox-list">
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Evidence of the <strong>functionality and effectiveness of the architectural provisions</strong>
</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Details of the <strong>functioning of building services engineering systems and controls</strong>
</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Details of the post-occupancy evaluation (POE) at the end of Years 1, 2 and 3 to establish feedback on functionality and effectiveness</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">POE results recorded with details of any required corrective action</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Evidence of a recognized method of calculation being used to provide an <strong>estimate of the expected CO2 emissions for the year</strong>
</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">
<strong>Annual review of energy use</strong> and a calculation of CO2 emissions that has been conducted</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">
<strong>Records of any fine-tuning</strong> or behavioral changes introduced to improve operational performance</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Details of any operational changes, where applicable</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Evidence that a comparison of <strong>actual and predicted operational costs</strong> is being maintained</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Records of any procedural changes made to improve operational costs whilst still delivering the required service levels</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Records of <strong>metered consumption of water</strong>
</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Records of <strong>measured waste reduction and disposal</strong>
</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Details of <strong>actual operational costs</strong>
</li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);"><strong>Documented experiences and lessons learned</strong></li>
<li style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);">Evidence that the findings from the first year of measurement of performance have been coordinated with the sign-off of the first year of the defects liability period</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="color: rgb(91, 107, 136);"><strong>Documenting experiences and lessons learned</strong>, together with feedback on performance, avoids the situation of valuable know-how disappearing when personnel leave any organization.</span></p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div>